PINKY(1)                         User Commands
PINKY(1)



NNAAMMEE
       pinky - lightweight finger

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ppiinnkkyy
       [_O_P_T_I_O_N]... [_U_S_E_R]...

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       --ll     produce long format output for the specified
       USERs

       --bb     omit the user's home directory and shell
       in long format

       --hh     omit the user's project file in long format

       --pp     omit the user's plan file in long format

       --ss     do short format output, this is the default

       --ff     omit the line of column headings in short
       format

       --ww     omit the user's full name in short format

       --ii     omit the user's full name and remote host
       in short format

       --qq     omit  the  user's  full name, remote host
       and idle time in short
              format

       ----hheellpp display this help and exit

       ----vveerrssiioonn
              output version information and exit

       A lightweight `finger' program;  print user information.
       The utmp file will be /var/run/utmp.

AAUUTTHHOORR
       Written by Joseph Arceneaux, David MacKenzie, and
       Kaveh Ghazi.

RREEPPOORRTTIINNGG BBUUGGSS
       Report bugs to <bug-coreutils@gnu.org>.

